HEADWORD: Castrato
<hw>Cas*tra"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., properly
p. p. of <ets>castrare</ets>. See <er>Castrate</er>.]</ety> <def>A male
person castrated for the purpose of improving his voice for singing; an
artificial, or male, soprano.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

